Arsenal captain Thomas Vermaelen has joined Barcelona for £15million, after the North London club refused to sell him to Premier League rivals Manchester United.

The Belgian defender has signed a five year deal with the Spanish giants, believed to be worth aroudn £80,000-a-week.

Vermaelen had been at Arsenal for five years, and captain for the past two seasons, but found himself spending most of last season on the bench behind Laurent Koscielny and Per Mertesacker.

